The problem is you have an HTML encoded Unicode character and what you want is the decoded version of it.  A library like [commons-lang3][1] (part of Apache Commons) will take your HTML encoded string and decode it for Java to display like this:


    String decoded = StringEscapeUtils.unescapeHtml(&quot;ji&amp;#462;&quot;);

You can also escape Unicode characters in Java like this:

    String jia = &quot;ji\u01ce&quot;;

This clever [one-liner][2] will take a Unicode character and show you its escaped form:

    System.out.println( &quot;\\u&quot; + Integer.toHexString(&#39;&#39; | 0x10000).substring(1) );


  [1]: http://commons.apache.org/lang/
  [2]: https://stackoverflow.com/a/2220476/16959

